{
  "doc_id": "28599",
  "text": "Flunixin presented a frequency of detection of 52.63% and was found in the range of ND-0.16 ng/L. Piroxicam, along with indomethacin, was detected at low levels (ND-0.16 and ND-3.19 ng/L, respectively), with a frequency of detection of 15.79%. High levels of piroxicam and indomethacin were observed by Collado Alsina in the effluent wastewaters from a WWTP in the range of 71-379 ng/L and 8-114 ng/L, respectively [CITATION_1] . High levels of indomethacin up to 40 ng/L were detected by Walraven et al. in coastal surface water from the Netherlands [CITATION_2] . NSAIDs have been extensively detected in seawater, surface water, and sewage waters worldwide [CITATION_3] . The detection of these substances in the snow samples may be associated with the treatment efficiency of the sewage treatment plant.",
